entries.femaleVariant: Goro? Took out the one closer.
entries.maleVariant: Goro? I took out the one closer.

entries.femaleVariant: The south end of the street is now secure.
Welp, that would be all.
Yes, apparently. Well done.
You are close. He is almost in front of you.
Just a few feet more, and he's yours.
A shooter patrols the footbridge.
Attention all units, I have suspicious activity in Sector 3C.
Understood, High Perch. Scanning the area...
Roger that, white jacket.
Low Perch? Militech agent at four o'clock.
Core to base. Why are two posts not responding?
High Castle, respond, do you read me?
Confirmed. A hostile agent.
The parade will soon start.
I will wait where we met before.
Take the footbridge at the top to cross the street.
The small door next to the pink neon sign – it leads to a maintenance path.
You will come out on the other side of the street.
You will find a door to a staircase at the end of the room.
It's the shortest route to the next sniper. He positioned himself high.
You will have to get down somehow. Just be careful.
Try to reach the maintenance area. You can climb up from there.
And if that doesn't work, you can use the footbridge to your right.
Watch out for the float jets. Unless you intend to get cooked, I would keep my head low.
I don't know how to open that. Look for another way.
As I said, get to the balcony with the green arrow. The sniper will be yours.
[Overload circuits]
By the stalls. Just stay outta trouble, OK?
Yes, I saw this. Smooth, as you say.
He is watching the crowd, not his back.
Won't know what hit 'im.
Keep you posted.
I am in position. The floats have started to move.
Remember to be careful or you will face Arasaka drones.
OK, good to go.
Fuck! Almost fell!
Carefully, you must not draw attention!
You must reach all snipers before Hanako-sama's float appears.
What do soldiers say? Target down.
Good words to hear.
One problem remains.
The Arasaka netrunner. She has taken control of all the networks.
You must get rid of her. We will not be able to hijack the float otherwise.
She hides in an unfinished apartment building, near to the second sniper's nest.
And that is?
I also spotted a netrunner in an Arasaka uniform. She is somewhere, hidden.
Then let us begin.
OK, on my way.
Bearded junkie next to the balloon stand. See to him.
Patrol, hold position!
Balcony, two floors up. Woman in red. I think she's armed.
Abort, I repeat – abort. She's holding binoculars. Collect the junkie.
High Castle, I repeat – do you read?
Core to base. Something is wrong. We have no response from High Castle. Recon required.
Have they been withdrawn? Reconnaissance required.
Watch him – the parade's head is about to arrive.
Those pipes look strong. Try to climb them.
Be careful – this is a construction area.
We would not want the workers to alert security.
V? It is Oda again! Listen!
We have to announce that public safety has been compromised! She must be extracted! At once!
Arasaka is fully capable of protecting its principals.
The situation is in hand. Over and out.
Did you hear? They know something. Perhaps much! We must hurry.
Ask your boss what he values more – the Arasaka image or his sister's life!
Got it open.
Words one likes to hear from a thief who is your ally.
Yes, just so.
Don't rush.
I need you alive, not a corpse below.
Now you must leap to the balcony by the green arrow and take the elevator.
